# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 12: COMPLETE TEST SCENARIOS
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### SCENARIO A: Complete Transfer Flow
# 1. Create accounts (Section 1)
# 2. Initiate transfer (Section 2)
# 3. Check status (Section 4)
# 4. View audit trail (Section 10)

### SCENARIO B: Pause/Resume Flow
# 1. Create accounts (Section 1)
# 2. Start transfer (Section 2)
# 3. IMMEDIATELY pause (Section 5.1) - within 10 seconds!
# 4. Check status (Section 5.4)
# 5. Resume (Section 5.2)
# 6. Verify completion (Section 4)

### SCENARIO C: Scheduled Transfer
# 1. Create accounts (Section 1)
# 2. Start delayed transfer (Section 3.1)
# 3. IMMEDIATELY cancel (Section 3.2) - within delay period!
# 4. Verify cancellation (Section 5.4)

### SCENARIO D: Idempotency Test
# 1. Create accounts (Section 1)
# 2. Send transfer with idempotency key (Section 8.1)
# 3. Send same request again (Section 8.2)
# 4. Verify same transfer ID returned

### SCENARIO E: Search & Analytics
# 1. Create multiple transfers (Section 2)
# 2. Search by account (Section 7.1)
# 3. Search by amount (Section 7.2)
# 4. Get analytics (Section 7.4)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TIPS & BEST PRACTICES
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# 1. TIMING IS CRITICAL:
#    - Debit operation: 10 second delay
#    - Credit operation: 10 second delay
#    - Total execution: ~20 seconds
#    - Pause/Resume must be done within first 10 seconds!
#
# 2. WORKFLOW IDs:
#    - Automatically captured in variables
#    - Use {{workflowId}} in subsequent requests
#    - Don't manually edit captured values
#
# 3. IDEMPOTENCY:
#    - Use X-Idempotency-Key header for idempotent operations
#    - Prevents duplicate transfers from network retries
#
# 4. SEARCH ATTRIBUTES:
#    - Work in production (must be registered in Temporal)
#    - Automatically skipped in test environments
#    - Don't cause failures if not configured
#
# 5. ERROR HANDLING:
#    - All endpoints return proper HTTP status codes
#    - Error messages are descriptive
#    - Feature flags return 503 when disabled
#
# ============================================================================
